cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper focuses on the fundamental property of reachability in time-varying graphs and proposes algorithms for controlling the progress of a packet in single-copy adaptive routing schemes. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses various types of networks, including social and information networks, and their dynamic nature. It also studies the loss of accuracy in probabilistic settings between different temporal graph models. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes algorithms for controlling the progress of a packet in dynamic random graphs, which are commonly used in networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the dynamics of networks and proposes algorithms for controlling the progress of a packet in dynamic random graphs, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper characterizes the latency of routing in time-varying graphs and proposes algorithms for controlling the progress of a packet, which can be seen as an information theory problem.
